---
title: Eastern European-Inspired Beef Piroshki  with Chive Sour Cream
description: Piroshki are delightful – they're golden pockets of joy filled with a savoury mix of ground meat, onions and spices, all wrapped in pillowy soft dough. These scrumptious pastries can be baked or fried, delivering a burst of flavour with every bite. Perfect for any occasion, enjoy them warm with a dollop of sour cream for an extra zing.

Ingredients: Pizza dough (enriched wheat flour (wheat flour, niacin, reduced iron, ascorbic acid, thiamine mononitrate, riboflavin, amylase, folic acid), water, semolina, canola oil, sugar, yeast, salt, calcium propionate, sodium stearoyl-2- lactylate, calcium sulphate) (wheat) • Ground beef • Carrots • Sour cream (milk ingredients, modified milk ingredients, modified cornstarch, sodium phosphate, sodium citrate, carrageenan, locust bean gum, guar gum, microbial enzyme, bacterial culture) (milk) • Green cabbage • Yellow onion • Grade A egg • Red wine vinegar (wine vinegar, potassium sorbate, sulphites) (sulphites) • Chives • Garlic • Smoked paprika-garlic blend (smoked paprika, garlic powder, silicon dioxide) (sulphites) • Dill-garlic spice blend (dehydrated onion, dehydrated garlic, salt, dill weed, canola oil, silicon dioxide) (sulphites).
